<br>
<br>
Baking -<br>
Unless you can forage, forget it. You're going to miss out on way to many recipes due to not being able to get the foraged ingredients yourself. Buying foraged ingredients isn't as easy as it looks. While you probably can get some of the more common ones, zone specific forages are next to impossible to buy in quanity simply because it requires someone to stand around in that one zone for hours trying to forage that special thing. Recipes that do not call for foraged ingredients, will call for mob drop ingredients.<br>
<br>
Brewing -<br>
This has a similar problem as baking due to some recipes calling for foraged ingredients. Although this skill is easy and cheap to raise, it also gets very click intensive. To get anything over 188, you have to make one beverage that has 8 ingredients that cannot be stacked.<br>
<br>
Fletching -<br>
If you're not a wood elf, you'll be at a hudge disadvantage if you go over 200 with this skill. The only thing which has any market value at the moment is the wood elf cultural stuff. The rest of us can only use the acrylia based arrows for post 202 skill ups.<br>
<br>
Jewelcraft -<br>
It used to be that you would spend a forture getting to 250, then would make it all back within a week. The market for jewelry has bottomed out a lot, especially since there have not been any major new items. Though it does have new complementry items.<br>
<br>
Pottery -<br>
This skill used to suck and have no redeaming value. With Velious, it sucked and had no redeaming value except Thurgadin Gate Potions. If you are willing to go over 200 in pottery though, there are a lot of nice things that you can make that people are interested in buying, such as the gate idols.<br>
<br>
Smithing -<br>
Don't let people fool you, if you have good charisma and ally faction merchants - this skill is very cheap to get to 175. After that, it gets painful and difficult. Unfortunately though, the market for smithed items is not that big as blacksmith produced items remain very expensive to make. The market for banded armour is ever shrinking.<br>
<br>
Tailoring -<br>
Lake baking, this skill requires a lot of foraged and/or mob drop ingredients. Like fletching, wood elves have a cultural advantage. If you can stomach acrylia farming, there is a market for that stuff at the moment and it is a way to make plat.<br>
